article.description: Jarrod West registered 18 points as Marshall snapped a three-game losing streak, easily beating Division II Bluefield State 86-50 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: West scores 18 to lift Marshall over Bluefield State 86-50
article.linkText: West scores 18 to lift Marshall over Bluefield State 86-50
article.story: HUNTINGTON, W.Va. -- Jarrod West registered 18 points as Marshall snapped a three-game losing streak, easily beating Division II Bluefield State 86-50 on Wednesday night. Mikel Beyers had 13 points for Marshall (3-6). Goran Miladinovic added 10 points. Marquez Cooper had 13 points for the Big Blues. Chris Knight added 12 points. Marshall faces Morehead State on the road on Monday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- Elements of this was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
